<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="239" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,573,1069]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,681,708]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[328,551,682,708]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphyonidae" genus="Barathronus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bruuni">
<emphasis box="[328,551,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Barathronus bruuni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other five 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" authorityYear="1886" box="[856,997,682,708]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphyonidae" genus="Barathronus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[856,997,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Barathronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with pigmented peritoneum by the following combination of characters: dorsal-fin rays 81, anal-fin rays 73, pectoral-fin rays 25, long rakers on anterior gill arch 33, precaudal vertebrae 36, total vertebrae 86, no ventral flexure of anteriormost vertebrae, 3 fangs on vomer. A distinct brown streak in midline of body and a concentration of brown pigment between dorsal fin and nape. The rounded, 
<quantity box="[374,439,826,853]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long otoliths seen through of the skull.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="239" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,573,1069]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,861,888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Description.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus box="[454,552,862,888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">holotype</typeStatus>
is known. For a detailed description see 
<bibRefCitation author="Nielsen, J. G." box="[1006,1218,861,888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" pagination="1 - 89" refId="ref15930" refString="Nielsen, J. G. (1969) Systematics and Biology of the Aphyonidae (Pisces, Ophidioidea). Galathea Report, 10, 1 - 89." type="journal article" year="1969">Nielsen (1969: 51)</bibRefCitation>
. The principal meristic and morphometric characters are shown in 
<tableCitation box="[688,772,898,924]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="9.[151,239,477,503]" captionText="TABLE 1. Meristic and morphometric characters of Barathronus affinis, algrahami, bicolor, bruuni, diaphanus." pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,573,1069]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,933,960]" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Comparisons.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[371,593,934,960]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphyonidae" genus="Barathronus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bruuni">
<emphasis box="[371,593,934,960]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">Barathronus bruuni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shcherbachev" authorityYear="1976" box="[846,992,934,960]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphyonidae" genus="Barathronus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[846,992,934,960]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">B. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs by having more anal fin rays (73 
<emphasis box="[194,217,971,996]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">vs</emphasis>
54–66), more vertebrae (86 
<emphasis box="[532,555,971,996]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">vs</emphasis>
74–79) and origin of anal fin below dorsal fin ray no. 
<quantity box="[1150,1206,970,996]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" unit="in" value="10.0">10 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName box="[1211,1316,970,996]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphyonidae" genus="Barathronus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bruuni">
<emphasis box="[1211,1316,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">B. bruuni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and below nos. 
<quantity box="[204,303,1005,1032]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.826" metricValueMax="5.842" metricValueMin="3.81" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" unit="in" value="19.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="15.0">15–23 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shcherbachev" authorityYear="1976" box="[310,456,1006,1032]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aphyonidae" genus="Barathronus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="239" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[310,456,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="239">B. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
